## Root Cause Analysis (why live site still showed wrong content after 2026-05-27)

### Content Stats (numeric $2.4B+ etc.)
- `content.service.ts::listContentStats()` inserts `DEFAULT_STATS` if the table is empty.
- `DEFAULT_STATS` still contained the OLD numeric values (`$2.4B`, `12+`, `95%`).
- The live Neon DB had no rows (or had old rows cleared) â†’ `DEFAULT_STATS` inserted on first API call.
- Fix: `DEFAULT_STATS` now matches `seed.ts` (Pan-African / End-to-End / 6 / 3).
- **After deploying: run `npx tsx scripts/seed.ts` against Neon to replace DB rows.**

### About Page Leadership Empty
- `about/page.tsx` uses `deepMerge(DEFAULTS, DB_value)`.
- `deepMerge` replaces arrays entirely â€” if DB value has `team: []`, the merge returns `team: []`.
- DB `about` row was seeded with `team: []` (seed.ts line 385).
- `SETTING_DEFAULTS.about.team` in `content.service.ts` also had `team: []`.
- Result: `deepMerge` overrode the frontend `DEFAULTS.team` (4 cards) with `[]`.
- Fix: Both `seed.ts` and `SETTING_DEFAULTS` now supply the 4 org-unit cards.
- **After deploying: run `npx tsx scripts/seed.ts` to replace the about DB row.**

### About Narrative / Mission / Vision / Purpose
- Same deepMerge issue: DB `about.whoWeAre.headline` was "Who We Are" â†’ overrode correct headline.
- DB `about.mvp` had truncated mission/vision/purpose â†’ overrode correct full text.
- Fix: `SETTING_DEFAULTS` and `seed.ts` both updated with the Replit-correct full text.

